---
<Layout title="Understanding the Keyboard | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Learn how the harmonium keyboard is organized — white keys, black keys, octaves, and navigation. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Understanding the Keyboard</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-beginner capitalize">beginner</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 15 min · Lesson 2 of 8</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Understanding the Keyboard</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Learn how the harmonium keyboard is organized — white keys, black keys, octaves, and navigation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>White keys = natural swaras (Sa Re Ga Ma Pa Dha Ni)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Black keys = komal (flat) and tivra (sharp) swaras</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>One octave = 12 keys total (7 white + 5 black)</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Middle octave (Madhya Saptak) is where most melody happens</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Find Sa by looking for the white key left of 2 black keys</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>The Keyboard Layout</h2>
      <p>The harmonium keyboard mirrors a piano keyboard. White keys play natural swaras (Sa Re Ga Ma Pa Dha Ni) and black keys play the altered swaras (komal and tivra). This pattern of 7 white plus 5 black keys repeats across the keyboard. Each complete set of 12 keys forms one octave called a Saptak.</p>

      <h2>Finding Sa on the Keyboard</h2>
      <p>The easiest way to find Sa is by looking at the black keys. They appear in alternating groups of 2 and 3. The white key immediately to the LEFT of the group of 2 black keys is always Sa or C. Use this landmark to navigate. Once you find one Sa all other Sas are exactly 7 white keys away in either direction.</p>

      <h2>The Three Octaves</h2>
      <p>In Indian music the three octaves are Mandra (lower), Madhya (middle), and Taar (upper). Most melody is played in Madhya Saptak. In sargam notation a dot below a letter means Mandra octave, a dot above means Taar octave, and no dot means Madhya. Our web harmonium covers Madhya and part of Taar octave.</p>

      <h2>Reading the Black Keys</h2>
      <p>The group of 2 black keys contains Komal Re (C sharp) and Komal Ga (D sharp). The group of 3 black keys contains Tivra Ma (F sharp), Komal Dha (G sharp), and Komal Ni (A sharp). Notice there are no black keys between E and F (Ga and Ma) or between B and C (Ni and Sa) — because Sa and Pa are achala (fixed) notes.</p>

      <h2>Practice Navigation</h2>
      <p>On the web harmonium find all the Sa notes across the keyboard. There are 2 in our range. Notice how each higher Sa sounds the same but at double the pitch. This octave relationship is the same in both Indian and Western music theory. Now find all the Pa notes — they are always 4 white keys above each Sa.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>